          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>What Is A Step-Thru Electric Bike?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Different from step-over bikes, there is no top tube on the frame of a step-through bike. Therefore, it allows people to get on and off the bike in an easy and convenient way.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Is The Ranger Step-Through Bike Good for Commuting?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Why not? The Ranger is convenient and comfortable to ride. Its battery could cover a common commute range. Its fat tire could handle all kinds of road conditions. And also, it is foldable as long as you need it.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Are Step-Through Bikes Heavier Than Step-Over Bikes?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>A step-through bike may not be heavier than a step-through bike. How heavy is a bike depends on how the bike was designed. It does not depend on it is a step-through or a step-over bike.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
